OL,5,C2027
OL,7,FDarren Sheen, 39 and Fusion
OL,8,FEngineering Ltd, face a raft of
OL,9,Fcharges relating to a huge mound of
OL,10,Ffly-tipped waste that appeared on the
OL,11,Fnight of January 19 in Watery Lane on
OL,12,Fthe outskirts of Lichfield.
OL,14,FLichfield District Council's
OL,15,FEnvironmental Health officers
OL,16,Finvestigated and on 21 March 2025
OL,17,Fseized a lorry believed to have been
OL,18,Fused in the incident.
OL,20,FIt cost the council nearly #10,000 to
OL,21,Fclear the waste.
