OL,7,FFlytipping is the illegal dumping of
OL,8,Fliquid or solid waste in land or in
OL,9,Fwater. The waste is usually dumped to
OL,10,Favoid disposal costs.
OL,12,FThe pile of rubbish has blocked both
OL,13,Fsides of the road across a stretch
OL,14,Fcovering a number of metres and is at
OL,15,Fthe junction with Wood End Lane.
OL,17,FWhat is the law around flytipping?
OL,19,FFlytipping is a criminal offence in
OL,20,Fthe UK under the Environmental
OL,21,FProtection Act 1990.
